<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Thats so unscientifi its not even funny.<P>Anyway, here is my rambling for today : <P>Assumption/fact.<P>Dual weild = 40%<BR>Double attack = 50%<BR>Max dmg formula = (Lvl + Str + Skill) * rating + hard bonus.<BR>Hard Bonus Formula = ((Lvl -25) / 3)<BR>Avg dmg = rating * 2 + hard bonus<BR>Swift Speed = 40%<BR>FBSS speed = 15%<BR>Augmentation + FBSS = 25%<BR>Sunderfury = 25/36dly, haste. <BR>Sunderfury haste speed = 35-40%<BR>Dragon Spine Claw = 10/21<BR>Bloodfire = 11/24 + proc (we wont count them today)<P>test will be sunderfurry vs the other 2 weapon<BR>sunderfurry will be compare to the 1-h slash with fbss only, fbss + augmentation(the most common combo) and vs swift. (40%)<P>The time unit will the a theorical 1000unit.<P>The dly of sunderfury is between 22-23. At best its 22, at worse its 23 in my opinion from what I heard.<BR>Ill use the 22.<BR>Max dmg of a lvl 50 with 150 str with sunder is 108,<BR>Avg dmg using the above formula with 150str is 58.<BR>In 1000 unit you attack 45 times for 22<BR>Assuming that you always hit, and since hit % should be the same everwhere anyway,<BR>Thats 67 hit with double attack for avg dmg of around 3886 dmg.<BR>Max dmg is of course impossible to get on 67 hit but would be 7236.<P>The Dragon Spine claw is easy, same thing.<BR>Number of attack <BR>Dly with FBSS = 18, # = 55. <BR>Dly with FBSS + Augm = 16, # = 62.<BR>Dly with Swift = 13, # = 77.<P>max dmg = 48, avg dmg = 28.<BR>With DA = 72 atk * 28 = 2296,<BR>          90 atk * 28 = 2520,<BR>         115 atk * 28 = 3220. That is quite incresible btw.<P>Second hand then. Problem is that avg dmg on second hand is not the same that with first hand.<BR>For now lets say avg dmg is (11 * 2) + 8 = 30.<BR>Dly is 24,<BR>Dly with FBSS = 20, # = (50 * 40%) = 20. <BR>Dly with FBSS + Augm = 18, # = (55 * 40%) = 22.<BR>Dly with Swift = 14, # = (71 * 40%) = 28.<BR>With DA = 30 atk * 30 =  900<BR>          33 atk * 30 =  990<BR>          42 atk * 30 = 1260<P>both hand added<BR>Sunder     = 3886<BR>FBSS       = 3196<BR>FBSS +Augm = 3510<BR>Swift      = 4480<P>Because off hand equation is not the same has first hand, dmg will actually be a bit lower then that on the 2 weap combo.<P>But still, the advantage of Sunder is apparent without any haste buff, but with anything that look like a cof or a combo that give this type of haste, 2 eapon type will do about same dmg, and probaly taunt better, etc.<BR>There is the proc on the second hand, that will do a bit of a difference.<BR>With swift speed, its obvious that the claw combo will do more dmg + the obvious advantage of dual weilding.<P>Evidently, getting 2 god type weapon is tougher then getting 1.<P>On another hand, when I wrote this I was very tired, so it could be sb  <IMG SRC="http://www.baelish.aust.com/tritonforum/smile.gif"><P>I could live with any of these weapons easy  <IMG SRC="http://www.baelish.aust.com/tritonforum/smile.gif">.<P>Thorbadin
